cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with face alignment, which is a computer vision problem, and uses deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks and regression trees. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training ensembles of models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of a prior face shape and addressing occlusions and ambiguous configurations suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with image processing and manipulation, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of regression trees suggests the involvement of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
